<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Library</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/library.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/library.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Library" BORDER="0"></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>Famed San Francisco lawyer Melvin Belli filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy Dec. 7, 1995, listing more than $400,000 owed to various unsecured creditors, including his retired secretary and the company that printed his 1993 Christmas cards. The following petition lists the creditors holding the 20 largest unsecured claims against him. In a press release, the 88-year-old Belli attributed his financial woes to an expensive divorce, a messy partnership dissolution, and an unexpected delay in payments from the multibillion-dollar proposed settlement of breast implant litigation. </P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<PRE>
VOLUNTARY PETITION 
 
United States Bankruptcy Court 
 
Northern District of California 
 
Belli, Melvin Mouron, d/b/a Law Offices of Melvin M. Belli  
 
soc. sec. no. 550-22-3492 
 
e.i.n. 94-1244953 
 
30 Hotaling Place 
 
San Francisco, CA 94111 
 
(415) 981-1849 
 
Chapter 11 
 
case no. 95-3-4573 TC 
 
 
LIST OF CREDITORS HOLDING 20 LARGEST UNSECURED 
CLAIMS  
 
Following is the list of the debtor's creditors holding the 20  largest 
unsecured claims. The list is prepared in accordance  with Fed. R. 
Bankr. P. 1007(d) for filing in this chapter 11  [or chapter 9] case. The 
list does not include (1) persons who  come within the definition of 
"insider" set forth in 11 U.S.  C. Section 101(30), or (2) secured 
creditors unless the value  of the collateral is such that the unsecured 
deficiency places  the creditor among the holders of the 20 largest 
unsecured  claims.  
 
 
Kelly & Rossi; David Rossi (415) 341-7758  
 
1065 E. Hillsdale Blvd. Suite 225 
 
Foster City, CA 94404  
 
Nature of claim: Trade Payable  
 
Status: Unliquidated  
 
Amount of claim: 75,963.00 
 
 
Joyce Revilla; (415) 583-7284 
 
2580 Olympic Dr. 
 
San Bruno, CA 94066 
 
Nature of claim: Reimbursable Office Expense  
 
Status: Unliquidated 
 
Amount of claim: 46,005.00 
 
 
ABC Printing Service; Dee Toze (415) 952-8700  
 
