My commission expires:


AGREEMENT

This agreement is entered into as of the 31st day of August, 1995
("Effective Date"), by and between R.E.M./Athens, Ltd. ("R.E.M."), and
Hershey Foods Corporation ("Hershey"), DDB Needham Worldwide, Inc.
("DDB"), and Westwood One, Inc. ("Westwood"); 

WHEREAS, currently pending in the United States District Court for the
Northern District of Georgia is Civil Action File No. 1:95-
CV-2902-JOF (the "Civil Action"), in which the plaintiff is R.E.M. and
the currently named defendant is Hershey; 

WHEREAS, the parties desire to resolve and settle between themselves
the claims in the Civil Action and otherwise as provided for in this
Agreement; 

WHEREAS, concurrently with the execution of this Agreement, counsel
for R.E.M. is filing a dismissal of the Civil Action, with the
understanding that a file-stamped copy of the dismissal will be sent
to Hershey; 

WHEREAS, R.E.M. has provided Westwood with a list of the charities to
which payment will be made pursuant to this Agreement, and
concurrently with the execution of this Agreement Westwood is making a
contribution to the charities designated by R.E.M.; and 

WHEREAS, R.E.M. and Hershey shall issue a joint press release
announcing that the dispute between the parties has been amicably
resolved, and other matters as jointly agreed upon in advance of the
release in the form agreed to and attached as Exhibit A; 

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the covenants in this Agreement
and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency
of which are acknowledged, the parties agree as follows: 

1.  Except as provided for in this Agreement, each of R.E.M., Hershey,
DDB, and Westwood, for itself and its successors and assigns, fully
releases, remises, acquits and forever discharges each other, and its
allied, affiliated, parent and associated companies and its officers,
agents, attorneys, employees and servants from any and all claims,
causes of action, damages, obligations, losses and expenses of
whatsoever kind or nature arising out of any acts, omissions,
transactions, promises, agreements, facts or situations relating to or
resulting from the radio promotion that was the subject of the Civil
Action, the filing of the Civil Action or any press releases or other
actions or statements regarding the Civil Action and that occurred or
existed at any time on or before the Effective Date, whether or not
now known or suspected or claimed, whether in law, equity or
otherwise, and whether accrued or hereafter maturing, including, but
not limited to, any and all claims that were asserted or could have
been asserted in the Civil Action.  As between R.E.M. and Hershey, the
release and discharge encompasses any and all claims, causes of
action, damages, obligations, losses and expenses of whatsoever kind
or nature arising out of any acts, omissions, transactions, promises,
agreements, facts or situations that occurred or existed at any time
on or before the Effective Date, whether or not now known or suspected
or claimed, whether in law, equity or otherwise, and whether accrued
or hereafter maturing, including, but not limited to, any and all
claims that were asserted or could have been asserted in the Civil
Action.  R.E.M. and Hershey shall not make any claim or bring any
action against the other arising out of or in connection with the
foregoing released claims, and shall indemnify and hold the other
harmless for damages and liabilities, including attorneys' fees and
costs, incurred in defending any such claim or action. 

2.  Within fifteen days of the Effective Date, Westwood shall make a
contribution in the amount of $50,000 to charitable entities
designated by R.E.M. by mailing checks in the amount of $5,000 to the
ten entities designated by R.E.M.  Westwood shall provide R.E.M. with
a copy of the transmittal letters sent, and copies of the checks
mailed, to the charities. 

3.  Hershey, DDB, and Westwood agree that they will not use R.E.M.'s
name in connection with any commercial endorsement or promotion
without R.E.M.'s prior written approval. 

4.  The contest prizes offered in the promotional contest that was the
subject of the Civil Action shall be awarded.  Contest participants,
specifically those persons who called the "800 number" advertised and
whose names and addresses have been retained by Westwood or its
agents, employees or independent contractors, shall receive a
transmittal letter from the agency responsible for overseeing the
awarding of the prizes in the form attached as Exhibit B, and a copy
of the press release.  At no time shall Hershey, DDB or Westwood make
any other use of any list of names or other information obtained in
connection with the promotional contest. 

5.  This Agreement shall inure to the benefit of and be binding on
each party and its successors and assigns. 

6.  This agreement will be executed in four counterparts, each of
which shall be deemed an original. 

7.  This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the
parties concerning all matters and supersedes any prior discussions,
agreements or understandings, and there are no promises,
representations or agreements between the parties other than as set
forth in this Agreement.  The fact that the Civil Action is being
dismissed without prejudice shall have no bearing on the
interpretation of this Agreement. 

8.  The provisions of this Agreement, including this para- graph, may
be modified or waived only in writing signed by the party affected by
the modification or waiver.  No waiver with respect to any portion of
this agreement shall apply to any other portion of the agreement, and
a waiver on one occasion shall not be deemed to be a waiver of the
same or any other breach on a future occasion.  No course of dealing
by any party, and no failure, omission, delay or forbearance by any
party in exercising such party's rights or remedies shall be deemed a
waiver of any such rights or remedies or a modification of this
agreement. 

The parties have caused this Agreement to be executed by their duly
authorized representatives, as of the date first written above. 

R.E.M./ATHENS, LTD.       [SEAL]

By: ____________________________

Name:  _________________________

Title:  ________________________

