<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>The family of a man who was murdered after revealing his affection for another man on television's Jenny Jones Show is suing the producers for $25 million.  In this complaint, the family of Scott Amedure, who died of two shotgun blasts, claims that the Jenny Jones Show created "the risk of harm" that caused the murder.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<PRE>
STATE OF MICHIGAN

IN THE CIRCUIT COURT FOR THE COUNTY OF OAKLAND 

Case No: 95-494536-NZ
Honorable: Gene Schnelz

FRANK AMEDURE, JR., as
Personal Representative of
the Estate af SCOTT AMEDURE,
Deceased,

Plaintiff,

v.

JONATHAN SCHMITZ, WARNER BROS.,
JENNY JONES SHOW ,
and TELEPICTURES, jointly and severally
Defendants.

GEOFFREY NELS FIEGER (P30441)
Fieger, Fieger & Schwartz P.C.
Attorney for Plaintiff
19390 W. Ten Mile
Southfield, Michigan 48075
(81O) 355-555S
Fax: (810) 355-5148

PLAINTIFF'S FIRST AMENDED COMPLAINT AND DEMAND FOR JURY TRIAL 

NOW COMES the Plaintiff, FRANK AMEDURE, JR., as Personal
Representative of the +state of SCOTT AMEDURE, Deceased, by and
through his attorneys FIEGE+, F+EGER & SCHWARTZr P.C., and for his
First Amended Complaint against the above-named Defendants states unto
this Honorable Court as follows: 

1. That FRANK AMEDURE, JR., is the duly appointed Personal
Representative of the Estate of his brother, SCOTT AMEDURE, Deceased. 

2. That the Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ, was at all times relevant to
the above-entitled cause of action a resident of the County of
Oakland, State of Michigan. 

3. That the Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ, is presently being held
without bond in the Oakland County Jail, having been charged with
murder in the death of Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE. 

4. That the Defendant, WARNER BROS., is a foreign corporation, doing
business in the County of Oakland, State of Michigan, and for all
times relevant hereto owned, operated, distributed, produced,
syndicated and/or controlled the JENNY JONES SHOW. 

5. That the Defendant JENNY JONES SHOW is, upon information and
belief, a foreign corporation, partnership and/or business entity
doing business in the County of Oakland, State of Michigan, and for
all times relevant hereto did solicit, for the purposes of appearing
on the JENNY JONES SHOW, the Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE,
along with Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ. 

6. That the Defendant, TELEPICTURES, is a either a foreign
corporation, partnership, joint venture, or other business entity
doing business in the County of Oakland, State of Michigan, and either
owned, operated, distributed, produced, syndicated and/or controlled
the production of the Defendant JENNY JONES SHOW. 

7. That on or about March 9, 1995, as a proximate result of the
negligence of the Defendants, and each of them, Defendant JONATHAN
SCHMITZ shot the Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE, twice in the
chest at close range. 

8. That the Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE, after suffering
unimaginable conscious pain and suffering, died of the injuries
infl1cted upvn him by the Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ; all as a result
of the negligence of each of the defendants herein. 

9. That the amount in controversy exceeds the jurisdictional amount of
Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), and that the amount of Plaintiff's
damages in this case exceed Twenty-five Million Dollars
($25,000,000.00). 

COUNT I

Negligence, Gross Negligence and Willful and Wanton Misconduct on the
Part of All Defendants 

1O. Plaintiff repeats and incorporates by reference each and every
allegation contained in Paragraphs 1 through 9 as lf stated
hereinafter in full. 

11. That at some time prior to March 6, 1995, a representative of the
Defendants, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and/or TELEPICTURES,
and/or each of them, solicited Plaintiff's Decedent SCOTT AMEDURE, and
Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ to appear on the Defendant JENNY JONES
SHOW. 

12. That the Defendants WARNER BROS./THE JENNY JONES SHOW and/or
TELEPICTURES informed SCOTT AMEDURE, his friend Donna Riley and
Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ, that the theme of the show was to be
"secret crushes", and further, that Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ wa8 to
be informed of the fact that he had a "secret admirer" who would be
revealed on the show. 

13. That at no time was the Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ, informed by
Defendants WARNER BROS., JENNY JONES SHOW, TELEPICTURES and/or
representatives of the Defendants that the true subject of the show
was "same sex crushes" or "same sex admirers". In fact, this
information was intentionally withheld from Defendant SCHMITZ. 

14. That despite constant inquiries by the Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ
to the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW, TELEPICTURES,
and/or representatives of same, said Defendants failed to reveal,
though repeatedly asked, the true nature of the show and/or that the
"secret admirer" of the Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ was a man. 

15. That the Flaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE, and Donna Riley,
prior to March 6, 1995, were interviewed by representatives of the
Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and/or TELEPICTURES, and
were specifically instructed not to discuss their appearance on the
show with Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ, or the fact that JONATHAN
SCHMITZ "secret admirer" was a man. Donna Riley and Plalntiff's
Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE, were further instructed in conversations
between themselves and the defendants, WARNER BRO.S., THE JENNY JONES
SHOW and/or TELEPICTURES and/or their representatives that they should
not plan on coming to Chicago if they were not prepared to make the
show "really good". 

16. That in furtherance of the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY
JONES SHOW and TELEPICTURES and/or their representatives' plans to
make the production of the show more scandalous, the Plaintiff's
Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE was encouraged to create fantasies involving
JONATHAN SCHMITZ. In fact, the true purpose of the show was to
sensationalize the fact that the Plaintiff's Decedent SCOTT AMEDURE
had a "same sex crush" on Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ. Furthermore, the
intent was to scandalize, embarrass and humiliate Defendant SCHMITZ. 

17. That the intended result of such scandalous revelations was the
desire on the part of the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES
SHOW and TELEPICTURES and/or their representatives, and each of them,
to create an audience reaction which included ridicule, outraqe,
hysteria and/or other strong emotion intended to improve ratings. 

18. That the defendants, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and/or
TELEPICTURES, and each of them, arranged for the Plaintiff's decedent,
SCOTT AMEDURE, along with Donna Riley and Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ
to arrive in Chicago on or about the date March 6, 1995. 

19. That after arriving in Chicago, Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT
AMEDURE and Donna Riley were lnformed by Defendant WARNER BROS., THE
JENNY JONES SHOW and/or TELEPICTURES, by their representatives, that
SCOTT AMEDURE must not fail to sensationalize his "same sex crush"
during the production of the show. Further, Plaintiff's decedent,
SCOTT AMEDURE was specifically instructed by representatives of the
Defendants, WARNER BROS., TXE JENNY JONES SHOW and TELEPICTURES that
he was to sensationalize the fact that he had a "same sex crush" on
Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ so as to increase the likelihood of a
strong audience reaction. 

20. That Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE, was encouraged by agents
of the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and TELEPICTURES
to publicly kiss JONATHAN SCHMITZ upon revealing that. he had a "same
sex crush" upon him, or, in the alternative, give him flowers and put
his arms out and hug him. 

21. That the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and
TELEPICTURES, in order to secure the sensational, scandalous and
"audience attractive" conduct which they intended, provided free
liquor to the Plaintiff's Decedent SCOTT AMEDURE in advance of the
show so as to reduce inhibitions and/or embarrassment, and to increase
the likelihood of scandalous conduct intended to humiliate and/or
embarrass Defendant SCHMITZ. 

22. That during the production of the aforesaid JENNY JONES SHOW, on
or about Monday, March 5, 1995, the Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT
AMEDURE, did reveal to the defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ, and upon the
instigatlon of the Defendanls, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and
TELEPICTURES, his "same sex crush" on Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ.
Defendant SCHMITZ had no prior knowledge of same and was
obviously-embarrassed by such revelation. 

23. That subsequent to the production of the show, no attempt was made
to determine the impact of the scandalous revelations upon the
Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ, by defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY
JONES SHOW and TELEPICTURES and/or any of their representatives. 

24. That during the plane ride back to Michigan from Chicago, the
Defendant, JONATHAN SCHMITZ was heard to comment to a fellow passenger
that "the longer I think about this, the angrier I could get." 

25. That on or about March 9, 1995, as a direct and proximate result
of the negligence of the Defendants, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES
SHOW and TELEPICTURES, and/or their representatives, and as a direct
and proximate result of the negligent and/or intentional conduct of
the Defendants JONATHAN SCHMITZ, SCOTT AMEDURE was shot twice at close
range to death with a newly purchased shotgun. 

26. That in a 911 call to an operator moments after the Defendant
SCHMIT2 had killed SCOTT AMEDURE, MR. SCHMITZ stated that the reason
that he had killed the Plaintiff's Decedent was berause "he fucked me
on national T.V." 

27. That the Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ further stated the to the 911
operator that the reason he had killed the Plaintiff's Decedent was
"because he played a really fucking thing on me. He put me on Jenny
Jones on national television". 

28. That the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES show and
TELEPICTURES, and/or their agents, servants, employees knew or should
have known that by their conduct and false representations, and by the
position in which they placed Plaintlff's Decedent along with JONATHAN
SCHMITZ, same would and/or could incite Defendant SCHMITZ, or any
person, to violence, such that Plaintiff's Decedent was unnecessarily
placed in a precarious and dangerous position as a result of the acts
of the Defendants as herein set forth, solely for the purpose of
improving television ratings. 

29. That the Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ had a duty not to negligently,
willfully and/or maliciously injure Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT
AMEDURE. 

30. That the Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ did willfully, negligently
and/or maliciously violate said duty by shooting SCOTT AMEDURE twice
at close range. 

31. That the Defendants WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and
TELEPICTURES, and each of them, had an affirmative duty to prevent
and/or refrain from placing Plaintiff's Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE in a
position which would unnecessarily and unreasonably expose him to the
risk of harm. 

32. That the Defendants, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW and
TELEPICTURES, and each of them, breached their duties in the following
particulars, by way of illustration, and not limitation: 

a. By way of extreme and outrageous conduct the said Defendants did
intentionally and/or recklessly cause severe emotional distress to
JONATHAN SCHMITZ, thereby foreseeably subjecting Plaintiff's Decedent
to bodily harm from SCHMITZ; 

b. Negligently subjecting Plaintiff's Decedent SCOTT AMEDURE to an
unreasonable risk of harm from JONATHAN SCHMITZ, which harm was
foreseeable in that a reasonable person could or should foresee that
the situation created by the Defendants, and each of them, would
humiliate, embarrass, and/or mortify Defendant JONATHAN SCHMITZ to
such an extent that violence against Plaintiff's Decedent would be
incited; 

c. Negligently subjecting Plaintiff's Decedent to the risk of
negligent and/or reckless harm by a third person, i.e. JONATHAN
SCHMITZ; 

d. Negligently failing to recognize that the conduct of the
Defendants, and each of them, would subject Plaintiff's Decedent to an
unreasonable risk of harm from JONATHAN SCHMITZ, even though such
conduct by JONATHAN SCHMITZ might be criminal; 

e. Negligently acting in such a manner so as to either intend, likely
effect or induce the described conduct of JONATHAN SCHMITZ such that
the Defendants, and each of them, knew or should have know that it was
likely that an unreasonable risk of harm to Plaintiff's Decedent would
be created; 

f. Negligently subjecting the Plaintiff's Decedent to an unreasonable
risk of harm by subjecting JONATHAN SCHMITZ to an emotional
disturbance of such a character so as to likely result in bodily harm
to the Plaintiff's Decedent; 

g. Negligently failing to provide to JONATHAN SCHMITZ  such
information as would allow him to make a full and complete informed
decision as to whether he should subject himself to the embarrassment
and humiliation caused the scenario created by the Defendants; and
further, by providing false information to JONATHAN SCHMITZ about the
true nature of the show in which he was to participate, thereby
subjecting Plaintiff's Decedent to peril as stated herein: 

h. Intentionally, negligently and/or unreasonably subjecting JONATHAN
SCHMITZ to such emotional distress which the Defendants, and each of
them, should have recognized would likely result in the risk of bodily
harm to Plaintiff's Decedent; 

i. Negligently misrepresenting to JONATHAN SCHMITZ the true nature of
the television show in which he would appear such that by such
misrepresentation, the Defendants, and each of them, foreseeably
subjected Plaintiff's Decedent to an unreasonable risk of harm; 

j. Negligently failing to warn Plaintiff r S Decedent, SCOTT AMEDURE
of the risk of physical violence to  him by JONATHAN SCHMITZ, which
risk would result from publicly disclosing AMEDURE'S feelings about
SCHMITZ as solicited and requested by Defendants; and 

k. Such other acts of negligence which may be disclosed through the
discovery process. 

33. That as a direct and proximate result of the aforesaid negligence
and misconduct of the Defendants, WARNER BROS., THE JENNY JONES SHOW
and TELEPICTURES, and each of them, as set forth above, Plaintiff's
Decedent SCOTT AMEDURE suffered severe injuries, conscious pain and
suffering, and horrible death. 

34. Plaintiff's Estate is entitled to recover such damages as are
deemed to be fair and equitable under the circumstances by those
persons who may be entitled to such damages under the Michigan
Wrongful Death Act. Those damages include, but are not limited to: 

a. Necessary and reasonable expenses incurred or paid by reason of
medical, hospital, funeral and burial expenses; 

b. Conscious pain and suffering, including mental anguish, fright,
shock, sorrow, hysteria and anxiety, endured by SCOTT AMEDURE during
tthe interim of time extending between the Defendants' wrongful acts,
and Decedent's ultimate death; 

c. Loss to the members of the Estate of SCOTT AMEDURE'S of his love,
society, comfort and companionship; 

d. severe mental pain, anguish and sorrow suffered SCOTT AMEDURE'S
survivors; and 

e. Loss to SCOTT AMEDURE'S survivors of support services and benefits
which they might reasonably have received from Plaintiff's Decedent. 

WHEREFORE, Plaintiff, FRANK AMEDURE'S, JR., as Personal 
Representative of the Estate of SCOTT AMEDURE, Deceased  respectfully
requests Judgment Against the Defendants, and each of them, in an
amount in excess of Twenty-five Million Dollars  ($25,000,000.00),
together with costs, interest and attorney fees  so wrongfully
incurred. 

COUNT II

Preliminary and Permanent Injunction

35. Plaintiff repeats and incorporates by reference each and every
allegation contained in Paragraphs 1 through 34 as if state
hereinafter in full. 

36. Upon information and belief, Defendant SCHMITZ presently has no
assets from which the Plaintiff could collect any judgment awarded by
this Court. 

37. The assault resulting in the death of SCOTT AMEDURE, are the
circumstances surrounding it, have generated extreme public and media
interest. 

38. Upon information and belief, Defendant SCHMITZ are persons acting
on SCHMITZ' behalf are currently pursuing the possibility of selling
his story to the media, in exchange for significant consideration. 

39. Upon information and belief, Defendant SCHMITZ plans to use any
sums received for his personal benefit, including paying for his
defense costs in legal actions arising out of the killing. 

40. It would be against public policy and offensive t equity and good
conscious to permit Defendant SCHMITZ to benefit from his crime by
allowing him to use any sums he received for selling his story for his
personal benefit, or to fund his defense against SCOTT AMEDURE'S
family in their wrongful death action, or to fund his defense in the
criminal prosecution. 

41. Plaintiff will suffer irreparable injury unless SCHMITZ is
prevented from disposing of any monies so received before such time as
the wrongful death claim against him is resolved. SCHMITZ is allowed
to dispose of newly-acquired assets, a wrongful death judgment against
him would become a nullity plaintiffs would be unable to recover any
damages and would be without any adequate remedy at law. 

42. The Defendant SCHMITZ will not suffer any harm by having any funds
so received held by the Court until such time as the wrongful death
action may be resolved. 

43. This Court may order equitable relief when failure to maintain the
status quo would result in injustice and would violate public policy. 

WHEREFORE, Plaintiff, being without remedy except in a Court of equity
prays as follows: 

A. That during the pendency of this suit, the Defendant SCHMITZ his
agents, servants, employees and attorneys and those persons in active
concert and participation with him who received notice of this Order,
be restrained and enjoined from using any money which receive from
selling, agreeing to sell, granting interviews or otherwise
disseminating information about the facts and circumstances
surrounding the killing of SCOTT AMEDURE, until such time as this
wrongful deal action has been resolved. 

B. That the Plaintiff have such other or further relief shall be
agreeable to equity and good conscience and as this Court shall deem
reasonable and proper. 

Respectfully Submitted
Fieger, Fieger & Schwartz, P.C.

Geoffrey N. Fieger P-30441
Attorney for Plaintiff
19390 West Ten Mile Road
Southfield, MI 48075
(810) 355-5555

Dated: August 13, 1995

RE-DEMAND FOR JURY TRIAL

NOW COMES the Plaintiff, FRANK AMEDURE, JR., as Personal
Representative of the Estate of SCOTT AMEDURE, Deceased, by and
through his attorneys FIEGER, FIEGER & SCHWARTZ, P.C., and hereby
restates his Demand for Jury Trial in the above cause of action. 

Respectfully submitted,
FIEGER, FIEGER & SCHWARTZ, P.C.

GEOFFREY N. FIEGER P-30441
Attorney for Plaintiff
19390 West Ten Mile Road
Southfield, MI 48075
(810) 355-5555

Dated: August 13, 1995
