<H2>Dan Abrams</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/dan.gif">Dan Abrams has covered trials for Court TV from all over the country, including the preliminary hearing of O.J. Simpson, the assisted suicide trials of Dr. Jack Kevorkian and the constitutional challenge to the government's policy on gays in the military. Before coming to Court TV in 1992, he wrote articles on gun control and the Second Amendment for The New York Times, The Nation and USA Today Magazine. Abrams is a graduate of Duke University and the Columbia University School of Law.
