<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Staff Bios - Raymond Brown</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Raymond Brown</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/ray.gif">Raymond Brown was a practicing attorney at the New Jersey firm Brown & Brown, where he will remain partner. The past president of the New Jersey Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers of New Jersey, Mr. Brown is a member of the Board of Directors of NACDL, a fellow of the American  College of Trial Lawyers and a certified criminal trial lawyer in the state of New Jersey.<P>
Mr. Brown lectures frequently at Continuing Legal Education Seminars and to community and educational groups nationwide.  He participated in the trial of former Labor Secretary Raymond J. Donovan and has tried a wide variety of criminal cases, including alleged white collar crimes and misconduct and homicide cases.  Mr. Brown has served as a Court TV guest commentator for numerous cases, including California v. Powell (the "Rodney King trial"), CA v. Simpson and Zion v. New York Hospital.<P>
Mr. Brown received a Bachelor of Arts from Columbia University and a Juris Doctor degree from Boalt Hall School of Law at the University of California at Berkeley.
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
