<HEAD>
<TITLE>Staff Bios - Frank Dehn</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Frank Dehn</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/frank.gif">Both an experienced reporter and a Harvard-educated lawyer, Frank Dehn has been utilizing his legal expertise to cover trials and other news-worthy events for the past five years.<P>
Prior to his career as a reporter, Dehn spent seven years working as an associate at a major New York law firm where he gained extensive litigation experience including courtroom work. He continued to practice law even after starting his broadcast journalism career, working as an associate for another major New York law firm from 1993 to 1995.<P>
As an investigative reporter in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina from 1991-1993, Dehn broke several exclusive stories and covered other important events including three capital murder trials. In the fall of 1994, Dehn worked as a special assignment investigative reporter for KTVE in Monroe, Louisiana where he exposed the truth about the operation of privately-managed prisons.<P>
Dehn is now a correspondent for Court TV: Inside America's Courts, which is in syndication nationwide. Dehn brings his legal knowledge and his investigative reporting experience to the field and into the studio, exposing viewers to the real-life dramas that unfold during civil and criminal cases in courtrooms across the country.<P>
Dehn completed his B.S. in International Affairs at Georgetown from which he graduated both magna cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa. In addition to his Harvard Law Degree, Dehn received a degree in Journalism from Columbia University where he was awarded the graduation prize for best video documentary.
