<TITLE>Staff Bios - Chris Gordon</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Chris Gordon</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/chris.gif">Chris Gordon comes to Court TV from WUSA TV Channel 9, the Washington metropolitan area CBS affiliate, where he served as a reporter since 1977 and as co-anchor of the "Eyewitness News at 5" since 1993.  He has received the American Bar Association Certificate of Merit for his news series, "Small Claims Court: A Consumer Guide," a Washington Emmy for Best Feature on a quadriplegic skydiver and two "Best of Gannett Award" honors, one for "Spot News" on the coverage of the 1989 Amtrak derailment and the other for his 1992 news series, "Who's Watching The Kids?"<P>
Mr. Gordon holds a bachelor's degree from the University of Rochester and a Juris Doctor degree from Cornell University Law School in Ithaca, NY.<BLOCKQUOTE><!--- full_end--->
