<TITLE>Staff Bios - June Grasso</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>June Grasso</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/june.gif">June Grasso has been reporting and anchoring for Court TV since its launch in 1991. She has covered trials from across the country and anchored more than 500 hours of live and taped coverage. She was also the legal analyst for the ABC Radio Network during the O.J. Simpson trial. Before joining Court TV, Grasso was an Anchor/Reporter for KITV in Honolulu, Hawaii. Prior to entering broadcast journalism, Grasso was a trial attorney at the New York law firm of Hawkins, Delafield & Wood where she specialized in communications law litigation. Grasso holds a law degree from Harvard Law School and a Masters Degree in Journalism from Columbia University. She is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Wellesley College.
