<TITLE>Staff Bios - Gregg Jarrett</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Gregg Jarrett</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/gregg.gif">Since 1982, Gregg Jarrett has put his courtroom skills to work as an anchor and reporter/producer for local news programs across the country. He has received honors from the Associated Press as well as from the Kansas Association of Broadcasters for his spot news coverage at KSNW-TV, Wichita. In September 1991, Jarrett won an Emmy Award for Best Coverage of a Breaking News Story for his reporting of a Kansas tornado. He can be seen as co-anchor of the nationally syndicated program, "Inside America's Courts." Jarrett obtained his law degree in 1980 from the University of California at Hastings College of the Law.
