<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Beth Karas</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/beth.gif">Beth Karas joined Court TV as a reporter in June 1994. Trials she has covered include Doe v. Kohn, Nast & Graf, Zion v. New York Hospital and Stone v. Toth. Karas also appears frequently as a guest commentator on the network. Prior to joining Court TV, Karas was an Assistant District Attorney in the New York County DA's office. She received her law degree from Fordham University School of Law and her B.A. from Mount Holyoke College where she majored in political science and Spanish literature.
