<TITLE>Staff Bios - Rikki Klieman</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Rikki Klieman</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/rikki.gif">Rikki Klieman was formerly a partner and is currently of counsel at the Boston law firm Klieman, Lyons, Schindler, Gross & Pabian where she specialized in criminal trial and appellate practice as well as civil litigation. Among her more high profile cases, she defended David and Ginger Twitchell, Christian Science parents on trial for manslaughter for the death of their child who received spiritual healing rather than medical care. More recently, she represented Katherine Power, a fugitive for 23 years who drove the car that four armed accomplices used to escape after one of them shot a police officer in a bank robbery. Kleiman received her law degree from Boston University Law School in 1975 and her undergraduate degree from Northwestern University.
