<HEAD>
<TITLE>Staff Bios - Helen Lucaitis</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Helen Lucaitis</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/helen.gif">Reporter Helen Lucaitis' career has continuously combined journalism and law. Following her graduation from Indiana University School of Law in 1988, Lucaitis went to work for the Indiana Attorney General's office where as a trial attorney, she represented the State in civil litigation.<P>
After leaving the Attorney General's Office, Lucaitis attended Northwestern University's prestiged Medill School of Journalism. Upon receiving her degree, Lucaitis went to work as a general assignment Reporter at Chicago Daily Law Bulletin where she reported on lawsuits, legal trends and politics for a daily legal newspaper. She later went to work for WFLI-TV, a CBS affiliate in West Lafayette, Indiana, where she continued to utilize her broad legal knowledge by frequently reporting stories which dealt with lawsuits and legal trends. During her time there, Lucaitis created and reported stories for "Legal Look," a signature series which covered consumer-legal issues. Lucaitis was also an investigative intern for Chicago's WBBM-TV where for three months, she worked undercover and researched the legal aspects of stories.<P>
Now a reporter with "Court TV: Inside America's Courts", Lucaitis uses her legal expertise and reporting ability in the field and in the studio as she brings her viewers closer to their country's legal system.
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
