<HEAD>
<TITLE>Staff Bios - Emily Mathes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Emily Mathes</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/emily.gif">Even while Emily Mathes was attending law school, she worked as a weekend television news reporter, continuing the broadcast journalism career she had begun seven years before.<P>
After completing her B.A. at Cornell, Mathes attended Northwestern's highly-esteemed Medill School of Journalism. Three years later, while working as an anchor, producer, and City Hall/ Courts reporter for WKYT in Lexington, Kentucky, she was awarded an American Bar Association Certificate of Merit for her July, 1990 series on domestic violence.<P>
Mathes also worked as a producer and reporter for both WMGT, an NBC affiliate in Macon, Georgia and for New England Cable News in Boston, Mass. In addition, she has worked for law firms in San Francisco and New York and was employed by the New York State Supreme Court. She received her law degree from Cornell in May of 1995.<P>
Mathes is now a correspondent for the daily syndicated news program, "Court TV: Inside America's Courts." Reporting from both the studio and the field, Mathes utilizes her legal knowledge and extensive reporting experience to provide information and insight into the dramatic cases covered by the program.
