<TITLE>Staff Bios - Terry Moran</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Terry Moran</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/terry.gif">Terry Moran joined Court TV from Legal Times, where he reported for five years on the Supreme Court and Judiciary Committees of Congress. At Court TV, he has provided viewers with in-depth coverage of the Clarence Thomas confirmation hearings and the Menendez trial, and is currently the host of Prime Time Justice, Court TV's nightly wrap-up of the day's legal news. Moran, a Chicago native, graduated from Lawrence University in Wisconsin.
