<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Staff Bios - Carol Randolph</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/ontheair.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/ontheair.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV On the Air" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Carol Randolph</H2>
<IMG HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=ABSBOTTOM SRC="/graphics/ctv/anchors/carol.gif">Carol Randolph brings 17 years of award-winning experience as both a legal and broadcast journalist to Court TV. Before joining the network in the spring of 1993, Ms. Randolph's extensive career began in 1975 when she was named co-host for the Emmy Award winning daily talk show "Harambee" on WUSA-TV in Washington, DC. Randolph went on to co-host a series of public affairs shows for the same station and in 1981 launched "The Carol Randolph Show." As an attorney, she was of counsel for the Washington law firm O'Toole, Rothwell, Nassau & Steinbach. She currently serves as a commissioner for the D.C. Arts and Humanities Commission. Randolph is a graduate of Washington University and holds a law degree from The Columbus School of Law at The Catholic University of America.
