<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Teen Court TV Survey: Censorship</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=FFFFFF LINK=000080 VLINK=FF0000>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="/teens/maps/tbuttons.map"><IMG
SRC="/teens/graphics/theader5.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL><P>

<H2>Teen Curfews: Necessary or Unconstitutional?</H2>

<FORM METHOD=POST ACTION="http://www.courttv.com/ctv-bin/chooser">
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" NAME="TYPE" VALUE="SURVEY">
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" NAME="TITLE" VALUE="surcurfew">
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" NAME="NUMBER" VALUE="10">

1. Who should decide when a teenager should come home?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="1" VALUE="A">You.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="1" VALUE="B">Parents.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="1" VALUE="C">The government.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="1" VALUE="D">No opinion.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

2. Do teen curfew laws violate the constitutional rights of teenagers?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="2" VALUE="A">Yes.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="2" VALUE="B">No.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="2" VALUE="C">No opinion.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

3. San Diego just passed a daytime curfew to keep teens off the streets during school hours.  Do you agree with this?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="3" VALUE="A">Yes, it prevents teens from skipping school.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="3" VALUE="B">No, this is unfair to teenagers.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="3" VALUE="C">I'm not sure.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

4. Do you think teen curfews are effective in lowering the rate of juvenile crime and juvenile victims of crime?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="4" VALUE="A">Yes, keeping teens off the street means they can't get in trouble.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="4" VALUE="B">No, curfews won't stop teens from committing crimes.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="4" VALUE="C">No opinion.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

5. What would you do if there was a teen curfew law in your city?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="5" VALUE="A">I would obey it.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="5" VALUE="B">I would still go out.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="5" VALUE="C">I'm not sure.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

6. Do you think that imposing teen curfew laws for the sake of lowering crime is more important than the right of teenagers to go out at night?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="6" VALUE="A">Yes.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="6" VALUE="B">No.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="6" VALUE="C">No opinion.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

7. The law prohibits teens from smoking before the age of 18 and drinking before the age of 21. Is it right to prohibit teens from going out at night?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="7" VALUE="A">Yes, just like smoking and drinking, staying out at night can be dangerous for teens.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="7" VALUE="B">No, teens aren't doing anything wrong by going out at night.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="7" VALUE="C">No opinion.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

8. How old should you be before you can go out after 10 p.m.?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="8" VALUE="A">Under 12.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="8" VALUE="B">12-14.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="8" VALUE="C">14-16.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="8" VALUE="D">16-18.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="8" VALUE="E">Older than 18.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

9. How old are you?

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="9" VALUE="A">12 or under.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="9" VALUE="B">13-15.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="9" VALUE="C">16-18.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="9" VALUE="D">19 or over.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

10. Are you:

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="10" VALUE="A">Male?<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="10" VALUE="B">Female?<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<INPUT TYPE=SUBMIT VALUE="Send">
</FORM>

