<BLOCKQUOTE>
<h2>Moderator Profiles</h2>
<!--- full_start: 632--->
<H2>Corporate Compliance: Standards For The 21st Century</h2>

<H3>Seminar Discussion Thread</h3><br>







<H3>Edward Dauer</h3>

President, <A HREF="http://www.pacificrim.net/~ncpl/">National Center for Preventive Law</a>. 

Dean Emeritus and Professor of Law, University of Denver.  Of Counsel,

Popham Haik Schnobrich and Kaufman.<p>



<H3>Richard Gruner</h3>  

Professor of Law, Whittier Law School; Trustee,

<A HREF="http://www.pacificrim.net/~ncpl/">National Center for Preventive Law</a>.  

His book, Corporate Crime and

Sentencing, was recently published by The Michie Company.  He is also

a newly added coauthor of The Legal Audit (1994 Clark Boardman

Callaghan), a leading treatise in the field of compliance monitoring

and preventive law.<p>



<H3>Kirk Jordan</h3>

President and Founder, Compliance Systems Legal Group;

Warwick, RI. Compliance Systems Legal Group assesses designs and

implements compliance programs for organizational clients. Kirk

frequently lectures and writes on corporate compliance issues.  He

spoke last month at the US Sentencing Commission Symposium in

Washington, DC regarding the compliance program criteria in consent

decrees and plea agreements concluded since the Organizational

Guidelines became effective.<p>



<H3>Joseph  Murphy</h3>

Senior Attorney, Bell Atlantic NSI; Philadelphia,

PA and co-editor of Corporate Conduct Quarterly and co-author of 

"Compliance Programs and the Corporate Sentencing Guidelines" (1994

Clark Boardman Callaghan).   Joe is a frequent lecturer and writer at

various national conferences on compliance.  He also recently spoke

at the US Sentencing Commission Symposium on the interactive roles of

government and business in compliance.<p>



<H3>Philip Sellinger</h3>   

Partner;  Sills, Cummis, Zuckerman, Radin,

Tischman, Epstein, and Gross; Newark, NJ.  Phil is a former Asst.

U.S. Attorney specializing in environmental and other complex civil

and white-collar defense litigation.  He is a frequent nationwide

lecturer on environmental compliance and internal corporate

investigations.



<H3>John Voorhees</h3>

Partner: Isaacson, Rosenbaum, Woods and Levy, P.C.;

Denver, CO.  

John is a former federal prosecutor concentrating his practice on

civil and criminal environmental law. He is an adjunct professor of

law at the University of Denver Law School and is a frequent speaker

and writer at national conferences on effective environmental risk

management systems and compliance programs.

