<html><head><title>Seminars - Principle No. 4 - Comply with Laws</title>
</head> <BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0005">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/smb.gif" BORDER=0>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<h2>Principle No. 4 - Comply with Laws</h2>
<!--- full_start: 668--->
<H2>Corporate Compliance: Standards For The 21st Century</h2><p>



<H3>Seminar Discussion Thread</h3><p>



From: Christina Cooley -- Counsel Connect - Atlanta<br>

Date:  Thu Oct 26 08:59<br>

Subject:  PR. 4-Comply with Laws<p>



<H3>NATIONAL CENTER FOR PREVENTIVE LAW WORKING GROUP DRAFT</h3><p>



<H4>Establishing Compliance Programs, Continued. . .</h4>



<I>Note:  Principle #4 and its Considerations are intended to

address the following aspect of the <a href=../../../../download/seminars/fsg1.html>

Federal Sentencing Guidelines:  Sec. 8A1.2(k)(1)</a>:  "The organization must have

established compliance standards and procedures to be followed

by its employees and other agents that are reasonably capable of

reducing the prospect of criminal conduct."</i><p>



<H4>Principle #4: An effective compliance program states that it is the

organization's policy to comply with all applicable laws.</h4>



Factors to Consider<p>



(a) Considering alternative methods that the organization can use

to effectively state its policies regarding compliance.<p>



(b) Stating the organization's goals and methods for achieving

these goals in a clear and straightforward manner.<p>



(c) Making descriptions of compliance policies and practices

readily available to all personnel who are subject to them.<p>



(d) Stating, wherever appropriate, that certain areas of law are

interrelated such that violations in one area of law may result in

legal obligations in a separate area.<p>



We urge you to submit comments and examples about the above

Principle.  To assist you in this, please review the postings

from the first day of the seminar, October 23, on the <a href=../../../../download/seminars/fsg1.html>Federal

Sentencing Guidelines</a>, the <a href=../../../../download/seminars/principle1.html>Full Set of Principles</a> and the <a href=../../../../download/seminars/model1.html>Model

Example</a>. Please note that the Principles and Considerations are

copyrighted by the NCPL and may not be reproduced without

permission of the NCPL.

