people (and hence organizations) do things wrong in the first

place. <p>



Without a program (at least the type defined by the FSG's), there

is little chance that an organization will stop to take the time

(and devote the resources) to give employees and agents focused,

quality training and communications on what it is they need to

know to stay out of trouble, and hence keep the organization out

of trouble, too.<p>



Now, I don't believe for a moment that everyone will leave their

pew after the sermon and sin no more, but it has been my

