From: Louis Brown -- Sanders Barnet - Los Angeles<br>

Date:  Mon Nov  6 18:34<br>

Subject:  small-medium business<p>



There has been some concern - and rightly so - about the ability

of small/medium business to set up Compliance Review... A

management feature to set in motion is to have as much of the work

done by non-lawyers as is feasible.... Doing it that way does not

eliminate lawyers... In a sense such a methodology follows the

approach that Woody Mosten espouses (See Wall Street Journal

article on page B3, Lawyers and Clients... today, November 6,

1995). Any comments?<p>



